.TH "HTMLDIALOGELEMENT.REQUESTCLOSE" "3JS" "January 26, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLDialogElement.requestClose \- HTMLDialogElement: requestClose()
method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]requestClose()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]HTMLDialogElement\f[R] interface requests to close the
\f[CR]<dialog>\f[R].
An optional string may be passed as an argument, updating the
\f[CR]returnValue\f[R] of the dialog.
.PP
This method differs from \f[CR]close()\f[R] in that it fires a
\f[CR]cancel\f[R] event before firing the \f[CR]close\f[R] event.
Authors can call \f[CR]Event.preventDefault()\f[R] in the handler for
the \f[CR]cancel\f[R] event to prevent the dialog from closing.
.PP
This method exposes the same behavior as the dialog\(cqs internal close
watcher.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
requestClose()
requestClose(returnValue)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]returnValue\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A string representing an updated value for the
\f[CR]HTMLDialogElement.returnValue\f[R] of the dialog.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using \f[CR]requestClose()\f[R]
The following example shows a button that, when clicked, opens a
\f[CR]<dialog>\f[R] using the \f[CR]showModal()\f[R] method.
From there you can click the either \f[I]Close\f[R] button to call the
\f[CR]requestClose()\f[R] method and close the dialog.
.PP
The \f[I]Close\f[R] button closes the dialog without a
\f[CR]returnValue\f[R], while the \f[I]Close w/ return value\f[R] button
closes the dialog with a \f[CR]returnValue\f[R].
.PP
Preventing the dialog from closing is demonstrated with a checkbox.
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]dialog\f[R] id=\(dqdialog\(dq>
  <\f[B]div\f[R]>
    <\f[B]label\f[R]><\f[B]input\f[R] type=\(dqcheckbox\(dq id=\(dqprevent\-close\(dq /> Cancel close</\f[B]label\f[R]>
  </\f[B]div\f[R]>
  <\f[B]button\f[R] type=\(dqbutton\(dq id=\(dqclose\(dq>Close</\f[B]button\f[R]>
  <\f[B]button\f[R] type=\(dqbutton\(dq id=\(dqclose\-w\-value\(dq>Close w/ return value</\f[B]button\f[R]>
</\f[B]dialog\f[R]>

<\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqopen\(dq>Open dialog</\f[B]button\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dialog = document.getElementById(\(dqdialog\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] openButton = document.getElementById(\(dqopen\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] closeButton = document.getElementById(\(dqclose\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] closeWithValueButton = document.getElementById(\(dqclose\-w\-value\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] preventCloseInput = document.getElementById(\(dqprevent\-close\(dq);

\f[I]// Open button opens a modal dialog\f[R]
openButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[I]// Reset the return value\f[R]
  dialog.returnValue = \(dq\(dq;
  \f[I]// Show the dialog\f[R]
  dialog.showModal();
});

\f[I]// Close button closes the dialog box\f[R]
closeButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  dialog.requestClose();
});

\f[I]// Close button closes the dialog box with a return value\f[R]
closeWithValueButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  dialog.requestClose(\(dqsome value\(dq);
});

\f[I]// Fired when requestClose() is called\f[R]
\f[I]// Prevent the dialog from closing by calling event.preventDefault()\f[R]
dialog.addEventListener(\(dqcancel\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]if\f[R] (preventCloseInput.checked) {
    log(\(dqDialog close cancelled\(dq);
    event.preventDefault();
  }
});

\f[I]// cancel event is not prevented, dialog will close\f[R]
dialog.addEventListener(\(dqclose\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  log(\(gaDialog closed. Return value: \(dq${dialog.returnValue}\(dq\(ga);
});
.EE
.SS Result
